"```sql\nSELECT DISTINCT Patient.ID, Patient.SEX\nFROM Patient\nJOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Patient.Admission = '-' AND Laboratory.HGB < 10;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects distinct patient IDs and their sex from the `Patient` table, joining with the `Laboratory` table to filter for outpatients (where `Admission` is '-') who have a low hemoglobin level (HGB < 10)."